!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

camera /ˈkæmərə/

(cameras) 

1. N-COUNT A camera is a piece of equipment that is used for taking photographs, making films, or producing television pictures. 照相机; 摄影机 

例： Her grandmother lent her a camera for a school trip to Venice and Egypt. 她的祖母借给她一部相机，让她在学校组织的到威尼斯和埃及的旅行中使用。 

2. PHRASE If someone or something is on camera , they are being filmed. 在拍摄中; 上镜头 

例： Fay was so impressive on camera that a special part was written in for her. 镜头中的费伊太令人印象深刻了，因此有一个专门写给她的角色。 

3. PHRASE If you do something or if something happens off camera , you do it or it happens when not being filmed. 不在拍摄中 

例： They were anything but friendly off camera, refusing even to take the same lift. 不拍摄时他们根本称不上友好，甚至拒绝乘同一部电梯。 

4. PHRASE If a trial is held in camera , the public and the press are not allowed to attend. 不对外公开的 [正式] 

例： This morning's appeal was held in camera. 今天上午的上诉是不对外公开的。

</div>

